HOUSE BILL 1000
F1 6lr3508
By: Delegate McCaskill Delegates McCaskill, Addison, Ebersole, Feldmark,
Palakovich Carr, Pasteur, Patterson, Roberson, Wilkins, and Wims
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 7, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Schools – School Mapping Data – Radius of School Grounds
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the school mapping data produced with funding from the
4 School Mapping Data Program to contain certain labeling that matches a certain
5 radius surrounding the school grounds; and generally relating to school mapping
6 data.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – Education
9 Section 7–1510.1(d)(4)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Education
15 7–1510.1.
16 (d) (4) At a minimum, school mapping data produced with funding from the
17 Program shall:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1000*

2 HOUSE BILL 1000
1 (i) Be compatible with software platforms used by the school and
2 local, State, and federal public safety agencies that provide emergency services to the school
3 without requiring the purchase of additional software or charging a fee to view or access
4 the data;
5 (ii) Be in a printable format and, if requested, be in a digital file
6 format that can be integrated into interactive mobile platforms;
7 (iii) Be verified for accuracy by a walk–through of the school
8 buildings and grounds;
9 (iv) Be oriented true north;
10 (v) Be overlaid on current aerial imagery;
11 (vi) Contain site–specific labeling that matches the structure of
12 school buildings, including:
13 1. Room labels;
14 2. Hallway names;
15 3. External door or stairwell numbers; and
16 4. Locations of:
17 A. Hazards;
18 B. Critical utility locations;
19 C. Key boxes; and
20 D. Automated external defibrillators and trauma kits;
21 (vii) Contain site–specific labeling that matches the school grounds,
22 including:
23 1. Parking areas;
24 2. Athletic fields;
25 3. Surrounding roads; and
26 4. Neighboring properties; [and]

HOUSE BILL 1000 3
1 (VIII) CONTAIN BEGINNING JULY 1, 2026, CONTAIN
2 SITE–SPECIFIC LABELING THAT MATCHES FOR BODIES OF WATER IN THE 1–MILE
3 RADIUS SURROUNDING THE SCHOOL GROUNDS, INCLUDING BODIES OF WATER; AND
4 [(viii)] (IX) Be overlaid with gridded x and y coordinates.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
6 1, 2026.
Approved:
